'''Elena Anne Corie Marchisotto''' (born 1945){{r|idref}} is a mathematician, [[mathematics education|mathematics educator]], and [[history of mathematics|historian of mathematics]]. She is a professor emeritus of mathematics at [[California State University, Northridge]].{{r|em}}

==Education and career==
Marchisotto graduated from [[Manhattanville College]] in 1967 and earned a master's degree from California State University, Northridge in 1977. She completed a Ph.D. in 1990 from [[New York University]].{{r|em}} Her dissertation, ''The contributions of Mario Pieri to mathematics and mathematics education'', was jointly supervised by Kenneth P. Goldberg and [[Anneli Cahn Lax]].{{r|mgp}}

She joined the California State University, Northridge faculty in 1983.{{r|em}}
At Northridge, she directed the developmental mathematics program.{{r|vargas}}

==Writing==
With James T. Smith, Marchisotto wrote a book on [[Mario Pieri]], ''The legacy of Mario Pieri in geometry and arithmetic'' (Birkhäuser, 2007).{{r|lmp}}

In 1995, Marchisotto became a co-author of an updated edition of ''[[The Mathematical Experience]]'' (a book originally published in 1981 by [[Reuben Hersh]] and [[Philip J. Davis]]),{{r|tme}} after having read the book and used it for her teaching from the early 1980s.{{r|csrh}}
She also co-authored an English translation of a [[history of mathematics]] by  {{ill|Umberto Bottazzini|it}}, ''Hilbert's Flute: The History of Modern Mathematics'' (with Bottazzini and Patricia Miller, Springer, 2016).

Marchisotto's textbooks include:
*''Topics in Intermediate Algebra'' (Wiley, 1987)
*''Developmental Mathematics: Arithmetic, Algebra, and Measurement Geometry'' (Wiley, 1987)
*''Mathematics for High School Teachers: An Advanced Perspective'' (with Zalman Usiskin, Anthony Peressini, and Dick Stanley, Prentice Hall, 2003){{r|mhst}}

