The journal was established in 1961.<ref name=nlm>{{cite web|title=Journal of Theoretical Biology |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog/376342 |website=NLM Catalog |publisher=NCBI |accessdate=11 September 2014}}</ref> Its founding [[editor-in-chief]] was English biologist [[James Danielli|James F. Danielli]], who remained editor until his death in 1984.<ref name=analysis-synthesis>{{cite web |last1=Poli |first1=Roberto |title=Analysis-Synthesis |url=http://www.metanexus.net/essay/analysis—synthesis |website=Metanexus |accessdate=11 September 2014 |date=1 September 2011}}</ref> Other notable founding members of the Editorial Board included [[Melvin Calvin]], [[Barry Commoner]], [[Christian De Duve]], [[Daniel Mazia]], [[Jacques Monod]], [[Conrad Waddington]], and [[John Zachary Young]]. The ''Journal of Theoretical Biology'' is published by [[Elsevier]] and, {{as of|2014|lc=yes}}, the editors-in-chief are Denise Kirschner ([[University of Michigan Medical School]]), [[Yoh Iwasa]] ([[Kyushu University]]), and [[Lewis Wolpert]] ([[University College London]]). According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2015 [[impact factor]] of 2.049.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=Journal of Theoretical Biology |title=2015 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
